        "type": "lesson",
        "heading": "HABER + Past Participle",
        "content": "All perfect tenses use HABER + past participle (-ado/-ido):\n                  → -IR verbs: vivido, salido, dormido = lived, left, slept",
        "examples": [
          {
            "spanish": "-AR verbs: hablado, trabajado, estudiado",
            "english": "spoken, worked, studied"
          },
          {
            "spanish": "-ER verbs: comido, bebido, leído",
            "english": "eaten, drunk, read"
          },
          {
            "spanish": "-IR verbs: vivido, salido, dormido",
            "english": "lived, left, slept"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "lesson",
        "heading": "Irregular Past Participles",
        "content": "Memorize these common irregulars:\n                              → morir → muerto = died",
        "examples": [
          {
            "spanish": "abrir → abierto",
            "english": "opened"
          },
          {
            "spanish": "decir → dicho",
            "english": "said"
          },
          {
            "spanish": "escribir → escrito",
            "english": "written"
          },
          {
            "spanish": "hacer → hecho",
            "english": "done/made"
          },
          {
            "spanish": "morir → muerto",
            "english": "died"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "lesson",
        "heading": "Present Perfect (Pretérito Perfecto)",
        "content": "Present of HABER + past participle:\n                        → Nunca he estado en España. = I have never been to Spain.",
        "examples": [
          {
            "spanish": "he hablado, has hablado, ha hablado",
            "english": "I have spoken, you have spoken..."
          },
          {
            "spanish": "hemos comido, han comido",
            "english": "we have eaten, they have eaten"
          },
          {
            "spanish": "¿Has visto la película?",
            "english": "Have you seen the movie?"
          },
          {
            "spanish": "Nunca he estado en España.",
            "english": "I have never been to Spain."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "lesson",
        "heading": "Past Perfect (Pluscuamperfecto)",
        "content": "Imperfect of HABER + past participle:\n                  \n   ✏️ Exercise: Cuando llegamos, la película ya ___ .",
        "examples": [
          {
            "spanish": "había hablado, habías hablado, había hablado",
            "english": "I had spoken..."
          },
          {
            "spanish": "Cuando llegué, ya habían comido.",
            "english": "When I arrived, they had already eaten."
          },
          {
            "spanish": "Nunca había visto algo así.",
            "english": "I had never seen anything like that."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "lesson",
        "heading": "Future & Conditional Perfect",
        "content": "Future/Conditional of HABER + past participle:\n                        → Si hubiera sabido, habría venido. = If I had known, I would have come.",
        "examples": [
          {
            "spanish": "habré terminado, habrás terminado...",
            "english": "I will have finished..."
          },
          {
            "spanish": "Para las 5, habré terminado.",
            "english": "By 5, I will have finished."
          },
          {
            "spanish": "habría terminado, habrías terminado...",
            "english": "I would have finished..."
          },
          {
            "spanish": "Si hubiera sabido, habría venido.",
            "english": "If I had known, I would have come."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "lesson",
        "heading": "Perfect Subjunctive",
        "content": "Subjunctive of HABER + past participle:\n                        \n   ✏️ Exercise: Si ___ ___ antes, te lo habría dicho. (saber, yo)",
        "examples": [
          {
            "spanish": "Present: haya hablado, hayas hablado...",
            "english": "that I have spoken..."
          },
          {
            "spanish": "Espero que hayan llegado bien.",
            "english": "I hope they have arrived safely."
          },
          {
            "spanish": "Past: hubiera hablado, hubieras hablado...",
            "english": "that I had spoken..."
          },
          {
            "spanish": "Si hubieras estudiado, habrías aprobado.",
            "english": "If you had studied, you would have passed."
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
